---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Words with Prefix ULTRA in Scrabble — Top Scoring Words & Bingo Strategy"
  description="Master ULTRA prefix words in Scrabble. Top plays include ULTRAVIOLET, ULTRASOUND, ULTRALIGHT. A 5-tile prefix needing only 2 tiles for a bingo — pure efficiency."
  keywords="words with prefix ultra scrabble, ultra words scrabble, ultraviolet scrabble, ultra bingo scrabble, ultra prefix strategy, scrabble words starting with ultra"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({ "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Article", "headline": "Words with Prefix ULTRA in Scrabble — Top Scoring Words & Bingo Strategy", "description": "Master ULTRA prefix words in Scrabble. 5-tile prefix needing only 2 more tiles for a bingo. Top plays include ULTRAVIOLET, ULTRASOUND, ULTRALIGHT.", "datePublished": "2026-06-23", "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" }, "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" }, "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/words-with-prefix-ultra" } })} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({ "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage", "mainEntity": [ { "@type": "Question", "name": "What are the best ULTRA prefix words in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Top ULTRA words include ULTRAVIOLET (14pts base), ULTRASOUND (10pts base), and ULTRALIGHT (13pts base). These are all bingo-eligible and score 50+ points with the bonus. ULTRA's low tile values (only 5pts total) mean extensions add the real scoring power." } }, { "@type": "Question", "name": "How many points is the ULTRA prefix worth in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "ULTRA is worth just 5 points (U=1, L=1, T=1, R=1, A=1). Every tile is a 1-pointer, making ULTRA one of the lowest-scoring prefixes by base value. The advantage is that all 5 tiles are extremely common in the bag, making ULTRA easy to draw." } }, { "@type": "Question", "name": "Can ULTRA help me get a bingo in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes — ULTRA is one of the best bingo prefixes because at 5 tiles, you need only 2 more to reach the 7-tile bingo threshold. Words like ULTRAS (6 letters) are short, while ULTRARED and ULTRALOW hit the 8-letter sweet spot. The 50-point bingo bonus makes any ULTRA word score at least 55 points." } } ] })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Prefix Guides</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Words with Prefix ULTRA in Scrabble</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-23">June 23, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>5 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">ULTRA is the common-tile bingo machine. All five letters score just 1 point each, which means they're the most frequently available tiles in the bag. You'll draw U-L-T-R-A more often than almost any other 5-letter prefix. And since you only need 2 more tiles for a bingo, ULTRA turns ordinary draws into 55+ point plays.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">5</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Prefix Tiles</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">5</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Base Points</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">15+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid Extensions</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">2</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Tiles to Bingo!</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top ULTRA Words by Score</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">ULTRAVIOLET — 14 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">11 letters. Beyond violet in the spectrum. V(4) adds strong value to the base.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">ULTRALIGHT — 13 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">10 letters. Extremely lightweight. G(2)+H(4) boost the score nicely.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">ULTRASOUND — 10 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">10 letters. Sound beyond hearing. D(2)+N(1) keep it modest but bingo-worthy.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">ULTRARED — 9 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">8 letters. Beyond red wavelength. Only 3 extra tiles needed. Clean bingo path.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">More ULTRA Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ULTRAS</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ULTRALOW</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ULTRAHOT</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ULTRAPURE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">The Common-Tile Advantage</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Every tile in ULTRA scores just 1 point — but that's the superpower. The bag contains <span class="text-white font-medium">4 U's, 4 L's, 6 T's, 6 R's, and 9 A's</span>. That's 29 tiles that can fill ULTRA slots, making this prefix statistically one of the easiest to draw naturally. Low value per tile = high availability.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">ULTRA Bingo Strategy</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Only 2 tiles to bingo:</span> ULTRA + ED = ULTRARED (8 letters). With just 2 common tiles, you're at 55+ points. The threshold is incredibly low.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">High draw probability:</span> Unlike HYPER (13pts) which needs H and Y, ULTRA uses only 1-point tiles that flood the bag. You'll see ULTRA combinations far more often.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Hold U-L-T-R-A:</span> If you spot these 5 tiles on your rack, play your remaining 2 tiles elsewhere and draw fresh. Your odds of completing a bingo on the next draw are strong.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Bingo through board letters:</span> If the board has an S, D, or N you can extend ULTRA through it. ULTRAS needs just 1 tile from your rack beyond the prefix.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">ULTRA Scoring Breakdown</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-amber-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">U</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">1 pt</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-2 py-1.5 text-gray-500">+</span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-amber-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">L</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">1 pt</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-2 py-1.5 text-gray-500">+</span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-amber-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">T</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">1 pt</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-2 py-1.5 text-gray-500">+</span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-amber-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">R</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">1 pt</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-2 py-1.5 text-gray-500">+</span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-amber-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">A</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">1 pt</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-2 py-1.5 text-gray-500">=</span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">5</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">total</span></span>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/words-with-prefix-hyper/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words with Prefix HYPER: High-Scoring 5-Tile Bingo Prefix</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/words-with-prefix-mega/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words with Prefix MEGA: Power Prefix for Big Plays</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-cyan-50 dark:from-blue-900/20 dark:to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find all ULTRA words instantly — enter your tiles and see every valid play</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
